The paper proposes a rule-based technique to generate natural language descriptions of OWL entities, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of ontology and DL constructs, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The generated NL descriptions can also be used for ontology validation, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of logical conditions and semantic refinement, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
